CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 17, 1956, pg. 19 reads: "frogs Set Example - The popular Frogs Club was the first organization to make table reservations for the Human Rights Dinner, sponsored by the local NAACP at the Gateway Plaza, March 23. Club members, wives and friends will sit at three reserved tables that night.  Officers, a visiting "Frog" and committee members of the club are, left to right, seated, Dr. C.C. Blow, Roland M. Sawyer and Dr. Royal W. Taylor.  Back row, same order, Dr. Max Johnson, C.D. Lownes, one of the "earliest" Frogs who was visiting, Charles Rickmond and William K. Leftridge. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: FROGS members, seated from left: Dr. C. C. Blow, Roland M. Sawyer, and Dr. Royal W. Taylor; back row: Dr. Max Johnson, C. D. Lownes, Charles Rickmond, and William K. Leftridge, gathered around two tables in interior
